definitions.definition: A large island off the coast of eastern Canada , which, along with Labrador , has composed the Canadian province of Newfoundland and Labrador since 1949, and the Dominion of Newfoundland , before it.
( historical ) Former name of Newfoundland and Labrador .
( informal ) Ellipsis of Newfoundland and Labrador .
( historical ) A former North American constituent country of the British Empire ; in full, Dominion of Newfoundland .
( historical ) A former North American colony of the British Empire ; in full, Colony of Newfoundland .

main_definition: A large island off the coast of eastern Canada , which, along with Labrador , has composed the Canadian province of Newfoundland and Labrador since 1949, and the Dominion of Newfoundland , before it.

definitions.definition: A very large breed of working dog from Newfoundland, with a shaggy , usually black coat, known for its water rescue ability, strength, and gentle disposition .
